    "summary": "I engaged in the diagnosis and treatment of severely traumatized patients for more than three decades, and teach and write extensively on the themes of trauma-related dissociation and dissociative disorders. \nI serve as a research consultant at Clienia Littenheid, Switzerland, and collaborate with several European universities. \nApart from research and clinical articles and book chapters, my publications include the book Somatoform Dissociation (Norton, New York) that also appeared in a German translation (Junfermann, Paderborn). With Onno van der Hart and Kathy Steele I co-authored the book The Haunted Self: Structural Dissociation and the Treatment of Chronic Traumatization (Norton, New York). This book has been translated in many languages (German Edition: Junfermann, Paderborn). A new book is The Trinity of Trauma: Ignorance, Fragility, and Control, Volume I and II. G\u00f6ttingen: Vandenhoeck & Ruprecht. The third volume of the trilogy is in preparation. \nThe International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation granted me several awards, including the Lifetime Achievement Award.\n",
